stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Booting : Awake (singleton, filter enabled ghosts)

    note right of Booting
        GameManager has no explicit state enum.
        These phases are driven by method calls,
        Invoke() delays, and Time.timeScale.
        Pause is handled separately by PauseManager.
    end note

    Booting --> Playing : Start -> NewRound -> ResetState

    Playing --> RoundComplete : PelletEaten and no pellets remaining
    RoundComplete --> Playing : Invoke NewRound after 3s (currentRound++)

    Playing --> PacManDied : PacmanEaten (Ghost collision, not frightened)
    PacManDied --> Playing : lives>0 -> DeathSequence + Invoke ResetState 3s
    PacManDied --> GameOver : lives==0

    Playing --> Paused : PauseManager Esc (Time.timeScale=0)
    Paused --> Playing : Resume (Esc)
    Paused --> [*] : Quit -> load PageAccueil

    GameOver --> [*] : panel + timeScale=0, NewGame -> PageAccueil

    state TrainingMode {
        [*] --> Episode : trainingMode == true
        Episode --> Episode : PacmanEaten -> ResetState (no GameOver pause)
        Episode --> Episode : RoundComplete -> continue (no 3s wait)
    }
